nstalled. Outdated or incompatible drivers can cause issues with IRQ routing tables. 2. Check for hardware conflicts: Verify that there are no hardware conflicts between devices, especially those using shared IRQs. You may need to adjust BIOS settings or change device configurations to resolve any conflicts. 3. Disable legacy support: In some cases, disabling legacy support in the BIOS can help resolve ACPI-PCI IRQ routing issues. This involves setting your system to use only UEFI (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface) boot mode. 4. Check for malware or viruses: Malicious software can manipulate system configurations, including IRQ routing tables. Run a full system scan with reputable antivirus and anti-malware tools to ensure your system is clean. 5. Repair or replace hardware: If the issue persists after attempting the above steps, it may be necessary to repair or replace problematic hardware components, such as the motherboard or power management ICs. 6. Consult with a professional: If you are unable to resolve the issue on your own, consider seeking assistance from a qualified IT professional or contacting the system manufacturer's support team for further guidance.","prompt":"[INST] Are there any errors or suspicious activity in the log messages found? Give a detailed response, and any resolutions that need to be done.[/INST]","context":"This data are from network log files. This log file data have been filtered using the search terms shown in the messages. The filtered messages may indicate potential suspicious log entries that could indicate a cyber attack.","pgptcontainer":"maadsdocker/tml-privategpt-with-gpu-nvidia-amd64-v2","pgpt_consumefrom":"rtms-preprocess", "pgpt_data_topic":"rtms-pgpt-ai","contextwindowsize":8192,"temperature":"0.1","pgptrollbackoffset":5}
